As a graduate of the Hotel School of Lausanne and now living in the Provence where I cater to a few selective people. I tried this recipe after having tried a few French Morrocan ones: This was the best that I have tried so far. The honey was too much. I would reduce it by half. Poix chiche or Chick pees are more Moroccan than almonds (almonds are from the south of France), therefore chick pees would suit the dish better. If one has a Cousance pot, reduce the cooking time by one to two thirds if not meat reduces to filaments. If using traditional Moroccan cooking platters the time is enough. Helen Ploderer-King - Orange, France and Salzburg, Austria

